1
00:00:44,277 --> 00:00:48,344
So this is the world, and there
are almost six billion people on it.

2
00:00:48,345 --> 00:00:51,368
When I was
a kid, there were three.

3
00:00:51,369 --> 00:00:53,349
It's hard to keep up.

4
00:00:54,705 --> 00:00:57,834
There. That's better.
That's america.

5
00:00:58,251 --> 00:01:01,379
See, America still sets
the tone for the world.

6
00:01:03,673 --> 00:01:07,219
In Indiana, Clark Hodd, 13, the
best point guard in the country.

7
00:01:07,741 --> 00:01:10,347
Last week he scored
a hundred points...

8
00:01:10,348 --> 00:01:12,327
in a single game.

9
00:01:12,328 --> 00:01:14,884
Erica Sorgi. You'll see
her in the next olympics.

10
00:01:16,814 --> 00:01:20,774
In Seattle, Dallas Malloy, 16.

11
00:01:20,775 --> 00:01:23,800
Her lawsuit helped pave the way
for women boxers everywhere.

12
00:01:23,801 --> 00:01:27,345
She's picturing her ex-boyfriend
right now.

13
00:01:27,346 --> 00:01:30,681
In Indio, California, Art Stallings.

14
00:01:30,682 --> 00:01:33,810
Check out what pure
joy looks like.

15
00:01:33,811 --> 00:01:37,772
In Odessa, Texas, the
great Frank Cushman.

16
00:01:37,774 --> 00:01:41,319
This april, 26 teams will be
falling all over themselves...

17
00:01:41,320 --> 00:01:43,770
to sign him in the
next NFL draft.

18
00:01:43,771 --> 00:01:46,219
He's my client, my
most important client.

19
00:01:46,220 --> 00:01:49,453
When are you gonna try? When are you
gonna concentrate? You wanna be a champion?

20
00:01:49,454 --> 00:01:52,479
Believe me, there's genius
everywhere, but until they turn pro...

21
00:01:52,686 --> 00:01:54,874
It's like popcorn in
the pan; Some pop...

22
00:01:54,876 --> 00:01:57,796
What the heck, coach? You don't
know diddly-squat about golf!

23
00:01:57,797 --> 00:01:59,360
Some don't.
You little shit!

24
00:02:01,342 --> 00:02:03,792
I'm the guy you
don't usually see.

25
00:02:03,793 --> 00:02:06,346
I'm the one
behind the scenes.

26
00:02:06,347 --> 00:02:10,310
I'm the sports agent. Wayne,
I'm gonna hurt you this year.

27
00:02:10,311 --> 00:02:12,290
How're you doin'?
I'm doin' fine.

28
00:02:12,291 --> 00:02:14,898
Listen, door's always open if you
wanna come and get a real agent.

29
00:02:14,899 --> 00:02:16,773
Thanks.
You're welcome, Johnnie.

30
00:02:16,775 --> 00:02:19,330
I'm gonna go to a meeting now,
and I'm gonna talk about you.

31
00:02:19,331 --> 00:02:21,312
'Cause I kill for you.
I'm an animal for you.

32
00:02:21,313 --> 00:02:23,866
We gotta win super bowls.
I hail you.

33
00:02:24,179 --> 00:02:26,264
Hey, Jerry, how're you doin'?
All right.

34
00:02:26,787 --> 00:02:28,245
How much is
this gonna cost me?

35
00:02:28,247 --> 00:02:31,427
You and I both know there's
a number you can afford.

36
00:02:31,428 --> 00:02:35,441
So I'm just gonna write it down, and
we can move forward from there.

37
00:02:35,442 --> 00:02:39,821
I can't afford that. No one
said winning was cheap.

38
00:02:39,822 --> 00:02:41,907
You know those photos...

39
00:02:41,908 --> 00:02:44,745
where the new player holds the team
jersey and poses with the owner?

40
00:02:44,827 --> 00:02:46,808
That's me on the left.

41
00:02:46,809 --> 00:02:48,842
Inside that building,
that's where I work.

42
00:02:48,843 --> 00:02:51,501
S.M.I... Sports
Management International.

43
00:02:51,502 --> 00:02:54,003
Reebok came in
with four million.

44
00:02:54,422 --> 00:02:57,498
33 out-of-shape agents
guiding the careers of 1,685...

45
00:02:57,499 --> 00:03:00,000
of the most finely
tuned athletes alive.

46
00:03:00,001 --> 00:03:02,503
You gotta be tough.
I already have 18 million.

47
00:03:02,504 --> 00:03:04,489
I handle the lives and
dreams of 72 clients

48
00:03:04,515 --> 00:03:06,518
and get an average of
216 phone calls a day.

49
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:08,290
It's what I do.

50
00:03:08,291 --> 00:03:10,630
I will not rest until I
have you holding a coke,

51
00:03:10,656 --> 00:03:12,827
wearing your own shoe,
playing a sega game...

52
00:03:12,828 --> 00:03:15,382
while singing your own song in
a new commercial starring you,

53
00:03:15,383 --> 00:03:17,832
broadcast during the super bowl
in a game you are winning.

54
00:03:17,833 --> 00:03:19,968
I will not sleep
until that happens.

55
00:03:19,970 --> 00:03:22,056
It's what I do best. I'll give
you 15 minutes to call me back.

56
00:03:22,057 --> 00:03:23,881
I'll be honest with you.

57
00:03:23,882 --> 00:03:26,436
I started noticing it a few years
ago and didn't say a word.

58
00:03:26,437 --> 00:03:28,416
Was
the girl 16 or 17?

59
00:03:28,417 --> 00:03:31,442
In the quest for the big dollars, a lot
of little things were going wrong.

60
00:03:31,443 --> 00:03:35,508
There's no proof of anything except
this guy is a sensational athlete!

61
00:03:35,509 --> 00:03:37,385
There was no girl!
That's bullshit!

62
00:03:37,386 --> 00:03:41,036
Are you Calvin Nack?
Can you sign my card?

63
00:03:42,287 --> 00:03:45,519
I'm sorry, little fella. I can't
sign this particular brand of card.

64
00:03:45,936 --> 00:03:48,334
Only pro-jam blue dot cards.

65
00:03:48,335 --> 00:03:51,463
I just wanted an autograph.

66
00:03:51,464 --> 00:03:54,382
Lately, it's gotten worse.

67
00:03:54,383 --> 00:03:57,930
Remo with the
puck, and... oh, he goes down!

68
00:04:00,432 --> 00:04:03,455
Hi, baby.

69
00:04:03,456 --> 00:04:06,479
Do you know your name?
Uh...

70
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:08,462
Steve Remo. Uh...

71
00:04:09,922 --> 00:04:13,571
Steven Remo.
Oh, wait. It's coming.

72
00:04:13,780 --> 00:04:16,492
My name is Steve Remo.
Yeah.

73
00:04:16,805 --> 00:04:20,974
I play for Chicago. This
lady here is my wife.

74
00:04:20,975 --> 00:04:22,955
Hi, baby.

75
00:04:22,957 --> 00:04:27,128
And this is my boy,
and this is, uh,

76
00:04:27,545 --> 00:04:29,943
Uh, uh, wait.

77
00:04:29,944 --> 00:04:33,072
My agent. My agent.

78
00:04:33,385 --> 00:04:38,494
I gotta play this weekend. If I play
65% of my games, I get a bonus.

79
00:04:38,495 --> 00:04:42,456
I gotta get the bonus.

80
00:04:42,457 --> 00:04:44,544
Okay, Jesse. You take
care, little guy.

81
00:04:44,961 --> 00:04:46,525
Mr. Maguire? Yeah?

82
00:04:47,046 --> 00:04:50,070
This is his fourth concussion.
Shouldn't somebody get him to stop?

83
00:04:50,383 --> 00:04:55,024
It would
take a tank to stop your dad.

84
00:04:55,025 --> 00:04:59,976
It would take all five Super
Trooper Vr Warriors...

85
00:04:59,977 --> 00:05:02,896
To stop your dad.

86
00:05:02,897 --> 00:05:04,877
Right?

87
00:05:04,878 --> 00:05:07,901
Right?

88
00:05:07,902 --> 00:05:09,988
Fuck you.

89
00:05:12,908 --> 00:05:16,662
Who had I become?
Just another shark in a suit?

90
00:05:34,494 --> 00:05:39,605
With the skyrocketing salaries, and
you are one of the guys responsible.

91
00:05:39,606 --> 00:05:41,534
Fuck you.

92
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:47,217
Two days later at
our corporate conference in Miami,

93
00:05:47,530 --> 00:05:50,554
- A breakthrough.
- I already had 18 million on the table.

94
00:05:51,075 --> 00:05:53,055
Breakdown? Breakthrough.

95
00:05:53,057 --> 00:05:56,186
- I just want an autograph.
- Fuck you.

96
00:05:56,187 --> 00:05:58,532
Do you
know your name?

97
00:05:58,533 --> 00:06:02,233
I couldn't
escape one simple thought.

98
00:06:04,006 --> 00:06:06,092
I hated myself.

99
00:06:08,074 --> 00:06:10,679
No, no, no.
Here's what it was.

100
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:14,226
I hated my place
in the world.

101
00:06:19,544 --> 00:06:22,985
I had so much to say
and no one to listen.

102
00:06:25,072 --> 00:06:28,825
And then it happened.

103
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:33,831
It was the oddest,
most unexpected thing.

104
00:06:35,083 --> 00:06:37,794
I began writing what they
call "A Mission Statement."

105
00:06:37,795 --> 00:06:40,087
Not a memo,
a mission statement.

106
00:06:40,088 --> 00:06:43,113
You know, a suggestion for
the future of our company.

107
00:06:44,572 --> 00:06:47,700
A night like this doesn't
come along very often.

108
00:06:48,013 --> 00:06:49,577
I seized it.

109
00:06:51,038 --> 00:06:54,999
What started out as
1 page became 25.

110
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,545
Suddenly, I was my
father's son again.

111
00:06:58,546 --> 00:07:01,623
I was remembering the simple
pleasures of this job...

112
00:07:01,624 --> 00:07:04,125
How I ended up here
out of law school;

113
00:07:04,126 --> 00:07:07,827
The way a stadium sounds when one of
my players performs well on the field;

114
00:07:07,828 --> 00:07:12,207
The way we are meant to protect
them in health and in injury.

115
00:07:12,208 --> 00:07:16,585
With so many clients, we had
forgotten what was important.

116
00:07:16,586 --> 00:07:19,610
I wrote and wrote and
wrote and wrote,

117
00:07:19,611 --> 00:07:22,113
And I'm not even a writer.

118
00:07:22,114 --> 00:07:25,711
I was remembering even the words of
the original sports agent, my mentor,

119
00:07:25,712 --> 00:07:27,693
The late, great Dicky Fox,
who said...

120
00:07:27,694 --> 00:07:31,291
The key to this business
is personal relationships.

121
00:07:31,499 --> 00:07:33,585
Suddenly it was
all pretty clear.

122
00:07:33,586 --> 00:07:37,130
The answer was: Fewer clients.

123
00:07:37,131 --> 00:07:39,528
Less money. More attention.

124
00:07:39,529 --> 00:07:42,761
Caring for them, caring for
ourselves and the games too.

125
00:07:43,179 --> 00:07:45,681
Just starting our lives, really.

126
00:07:45,682 --> 00:07:50,896
I'll be first to admit it. What I was
writing was somewhat touchy-feely.

127
00:07:50,897 --> 00:07:54,649
I didn't care. I had lost
the ability to bullshit.

128
00:07:54,650 --> 00:07:57,778
It was the me I'd
always wanted to be.

129
00:08:01,115 --> 00:08:03,723
I took it in a bag to a copymat
in the middle of the night...

130
00:08:03,724 --> 00:08:06,224
And printed up 110 copies.

131
00:08:06,225 --> 00:08:08,728
Even the cover looked like
the catcher in the rye.

132
00:08:08,729 --> 00:08:12,795
I entitled it, the things
we think and do not say:

133
00:08:14,255 --> 00:08:16,652
The future of our business.

134
00:08:16,653 --> 00:08:20,303
That's how you
become great, man.

135
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:23,222
Hang your balls out there.

136
00:08:23,224 --> 00:08:25,309
Thanks.

137
00:08:26,143 --> 00:08:28,645
Everybody got a copy.

138
00:08:28,646 --> 00:08:31,316
There are dangerous animals in the world.
Some walk on two feet.

139
00:08:31,775 --> 00:08:33,860
They don't want peace.
They're not capable of love.

140
00:08:33,861 --> 00:08:39,387
Society... and that means you and you...
need protection from these warped minds.

141
00:08:39,389 --> 00:08:42,307
♪♪

142
00:08:54,091 --> 00:08:56,280
Boom.

143
00:08:58,263 --> 00:09:01,808
Hi, this is Jerry Maguire.
Did those manuscripts get...

144
00:09:01,809 --> 00:09:03,789
They've all gone out.
Oh, they did?

145
00:09:04,206 --> 00:09:06,814
Would you like me... oh, no, no.
That's fine.

146
00:09:07,231 --> 00:09:09,316
Thank you.

147
00:09:11,193 --> 00:09:15,677
I could
connect you, if you'd like.

148
00:09:24,228 --> 00:09:27,357
Front desk.
How may I help you?

149
00:09:36,221 --> 00:09:39,975
All right! Hey, finally
somebody sane.

150
00:09:41,747 --> 00:09:45,188
- Good work, Maguire!
- Yeah, yeah!

151
00:09:45,189 --> 00:09:48,734
Yeah!

152
00:09:48,735 --> 00:09:52,697
Unbelievable.
Unbelievable.

153
00:09:55,826 --> 00:09:57,911
Oh, yeah.

154
00:10:00,310 --> 00:10:04,272
I was 35.

155
00:10:04,273 --> 00:10:06,774
I'd started my life.

156
00:10:06,775 --> 00:10:09,381
How long do you give him?

157
00:10:09,382 --> 00:10:11,469
'Bout a week.

158
00:10:20,854 --> 00:10:23,691
You're with the sports people on the plane?
Yeah, I'm Jerry Maguire.

159
00:10:23,774 --> 00:10:26,692
S.M.I. Bobbi Fallon, B.P.I.

160
00:10:26,693 --> 00:10:28,778
I'm producing the coke
commercials for the play-offs.

161
00:10:28,780 --> 00:10:30,969
Good luck with that.

162
00:10:30,970 --> 00:10:33,784
Oh, hi. Hi.

163
00:10:33,785 --> 00:10:36,808
My son is really allergic to
the material in the blankets,

164
00:10:36,809 --> 00:10:38,895
And I was wondering...
that's all we have, okay?

165
00:10:41,189 --> 00:10:43,900
Ohh!

166
00:10:43,901 --> 00:10:46,819
I'm sorry if I was
rude just then.

167
00:10:46,820 --> 00:10:49,843
That's okay. We're
in it together now.

168
00:10:49,844 --> 00:10:53,911
Why is it so easy to talk with you?
Tell me about your fiancee.

169
00:10:53,912 --> 00:10:56,884
More champagne? I don't think
we're at your pitch yet.

170
00:10:56,885 --> 00:10:59,046
Tell me how you proposed.
Honey, are you all right?

171
00:10:59,072 --> 00:10:59,985
You want some juice
or something?

172
00:11:02,358 --> 00:11:07,258
Thank you. But we're hiking
up through the pools.

173
00:11:07,260 --> 00:11:12,368
I got the ring in my pocket, and...
I'm a little nervous.

174
00:11:12,369 --> 00:11:16,019
I'm lagging, you know, and
she says to me... get this...

175
00:11:16,436 --> 00:11:17,896
"Hurry up, klutz."

176
00:11:18,313 --> 00:11:20,815
It bothered me
somewhat, you know?

177
00:11:20,816 --> 00:11:22,902
I got quiet and she got quiet.

178
00:11:23,319 --> 00:11:26,343
And I decide, I'm
not gonna propose.

179
00:11:26,864 --> 00:11:29,887
The mood is not right.
Why be impulsive?

180
00:11:29,888 --> 00:11:32,340
Now, at this point I
know she knows...

181
00:11:32,341 --> 00:11:34,842
That I was gonna propose and
didn't, and she knows I know.

182
00:11:34,843 --> 00:11:37,918
So we check back into the
pro bowl hotel. How sad.

183
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:41,463
No. But wait.
Little do I know...

184
00:11:41,464 --> 00:11:43,967
That my assistant has assumed
that I've now proposed.

185
00:11:44,488 --> 00:11:47,512
So she's gotten a lounge band to
actually play "Here Comes the Bride"...

186
00:11:47,825 --> 00:11:50,381
When we walk back in.
I love that song.

187
00:11:50,382 --> 00:11:53,039
All the football guys are
in the lobby, watching.

188
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:55,542
There's even an ESPN crew.

189
00:11:55,855 --> 00:11:59,087
So I turned to her,
sort of grandly say,

190
00:11:59,297 --> 00:12:02,319
"Well, this is me, klutz,

191
00:12:02,321 --> 00:12:05,970
Asking you, Goddess of rock
climbing, to marry me."

192
00:12:06,387 --> 00:12:07,951
I took out the ring.

193
00:12:08,369 --> 00:12:10,038
You know, I don't
much like big scenes,

194
00:12:10,455 --> 00:12:12,540
But, uh,

195
00:12:12,957 --> 00:12:15,512
She said "yes" right
there in the lobby.

196
00:12:15,513 --> 00:12:18,589
Some of the toughest men in
football wept like babies.

197
00:12:18,590 --> 00:12:21,403
We're gettin' married
in February.

198
00:12:21,404 --> 00:12:24,949
Oh, Jerry, you two
are gonna be married forever.

199
00:12:30,894 --> 00:12:33,917
What's wrong, mom?

200
00:12:33,918 --> 00:12:37,047
First class is
what's wrong, honey.

201
00:12:37,464 --> 00:12:41,113
It used to be a better meal.
Now it's a better life.

202
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:49,508
Mr. Waters,
Mr. Charles Waters, Ray!

203
00:12:49,509 --> 00:12:52,063
Your party is waiting for you
at the information gate... Ray!

204
00:12:52,064 --> 00:12:54,045
On the upper concourse.
Come on, buddy!

205
00:12:54,046 --> 00:12:56,026
High five! Ray!

206
00:12:56,443 --> 00:12:59,049
Oh, God. Ray! Excuse me.

207
00:12:59,050 --> 00:13:01,447
Can I help you?

208
00:13:01,448 --> 00:13:03,429
Jerry Maguire.

209
00:13:03,430 --> 00:13:06,974
I work in your office.
I was on the junket.

210
00:13:06,975 --> 00:13:09,582
I know who you are.
Dorothy Boyd in accounts.

211
00:13:09,895 --> 00:13:13,650
You have the side-middle cubicle with
the poster of Albert Einstein's face...

212
00:13:13,651 --> 00:13:16,464
Morphed on shaquille
O'neal's body.

213
00:13:16,465 --> 00:13:18,549
That's pretty good.

214
00:13:18,551 --> 00:13:20,636
Wh-what did you lose here?

215
00:13:21,054 --> 00:13:25,121
- My son, my mind.
- Ray!

216
00:13:26,580 --> 00:13:28,560
Ray!

217
00:13:28,562 --> 00:13:30,596
- Listen, while I look... Dorothy?
- Huh?

218
00:13:30,597 --> 00:13:34,610
While I go look for him, why don't you
grab this curious gentleman here?

219
00:13:35,444 --> 00:13:39,095
- Hee hee!
- Oh. Oh, thank God.

220
00:13:39,408 --> 00:13:42,535
Oh. Ohh!

221
00:13:42,536 --> 00:13:45,559
You scared me.
You scared me.

222
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:49,418
Don't do that again, ever!
Okay, mommy.

223
00:13:49,419 --> 00:13:53,067
Ever, ever, ever!
Okay? Ever!

224
00:13:53,068 --> 00:13:55,465
Dorothy? Take care.

225
00:13:55,466 --> 00:13:57,657
Thank you so much.

226
00:13:58,491 --> 00:14:00,575
I loved your memo,

227
00:14:00,577 --> 00:14:02,662
By the way.

228
00:14:05,060 --> 00:14:07,668
- You did?
- Yeah.

229
00:14:10,588 --> 00:14:12,463
Thanks.

230
00:14:12,465 --> 00:14:15,594
Uh, actually it was just a mission...
Statement.

231
00:14:15,595 --> 00:14:18,618
I think, in this age, optimism
like that is a revolutionary act.

232
00:14:18,619 --> 00:14:21,015
- You think so?
- Oh, yeah.

233
00:14:21,016 --> 00:14:24,040
I appreciate that because I
didn't know if I should write it.

234
00:14:24,041 --> 00:14:27,169
I mean, it was 2:00
in the morning.

235
00:14:27,586 --> 00:14:30,714
I don't know. Some of the
stuff, I just... whoo!

236
00:14:31,027 --> 00:14:36,137
No. That part about how we should embrace
what is still virginal in our enthusiasm...

237
00:14:36,138 --> 00:14:37,545
Uh... not right now, honey.

238
00:14:37,546 --> 00:14:41,716
And force open the tightly clenched fist
of commerce and give a little back...

239
00:14:41,717 --> 00:14:43,646
- for the greater good?
- Uh-huh.

240
00:14:43,647 --> 00:14:48,649
God, I was inspired, and I'm
