1795
01:55:04,802 --> 01:55:07,930
Get outta here. Go.

1796
01:55:09,599 --> 01:55:13,143
Where's your agent?
I don't know.

1797
01:55:13,144 --> 01:55:17,211
I know this is uncool to do this now,
but you belong with the big boys.

1798
01:55:17,212 --> 01:55:20,287
You belong with the big money. You're
fuckin' Rod Tidwell. Hey! Hey!

1799
01:55:20,288 --> 01:55:23,885
Get away from my guy. Hey,
Jerry, I was just hailing you.

1800
01:55:23,886 --> 01:55:27,221
Just go. Flee.

1801
01:55:27,222 --> 01:55:29,724
This is a nice moment for you.

1802
01:55:29,725 --> 01:55:33,269
I'm going to let you have it.

1803
01:55:33,270 --> 01:55:36,399
Give me a call, Rod.
Say hi to Marcee for me.

1804
01:55:44,220 --> 01:55:47,349
Thanks for coming.
I missed you.

1805
01:55:49,747 --> 01:55:54,023
What can I say? You're all I've got.

1806
01:55:56,213 --> 01:55:59,289
Hello again, everyone. Frank Gifford
with Al Michaels and Dan Dierdorf.

1807
01:55:59,290 --> 01:56:01,792
Welcome to Tempe, Arizona's
sun devil stadium...

1808
01:56:01,793 --> 01:56:04,242
Where the story
tonight is the Cardinals.

1809
01:56:04,244 --> 01:56:07,265
They are still alive
for a play-off spot.

1810
01:56:07,266 --> 01:56:11,334
The reason the Cardinals are alive is
the outstanding play of Rod Tidwell.

1811
01:56:11,335 --> 01:56:13,731
That's my daddy!

1812
01:56:13,732 --> 01:56:15,740
Meanwhile, the Dallas
Cowboys continue to roll.

1813
01:56:15,766 --> 01:56:17,329
They know they're
in the play-offs...

1814
01:56:17,331 --> 01:56:19,833
And going in looking for a
second consecutive super bowl.

1815
01:56:19,834 --> 01:56:22,440
Who could've believed this?
Here's the deal.

1816
01:56:22,441 --> 01:56:26,350
If Arizona wins tonight and next
week, amazingly the Cardinals...

1817
01:56:26,351 --> 01:56:29,375
will make the play-offs for
the first time in 21 years.

1818
01:56:29,376 --> 01:56:34,379
Whoo! Better not mess up
for monday night football.

1819
01:56:34,380 --> 01:56:39,385
What'd I say? Everybody knows he gets
nervous for nationally televised games.

1820
01:56:39,386 --> 01:56:42,410
The Cowboys continue their super
bowl mission on monday night football,

1821
01:56:42,411 --> 01:56:44,389
A Christmas edition.

1822
01:56:50,752 --> 01:56:53,359
Hey, Shannon.
Hi, Jerry. Good game.

1823
01:56:53,880 --> 01:56:56,905
Yeah. Hey, great column this morning.
Thanks.

