Boy, guys, it's a real
bruiser out there tonight.

1826
01:57:13,904 --> 01:57:18,439
The cardinals just refuse
to go quietly into the desert night,

1827
01:57:18,440 --> 01:57:20,942
As their seemingly interminable
season winds down.

1828
01:57:20,943 --> 01:57:23,497
Come on, guys. I'm trying
to be a little poetic here.

1829
01:57:23,498 --> 01:57:26,416
Wax on, Al.

1830
01:57:26,417 --> 01:57:29,857
Ouch! Oh, a tough
hit on Rod Tidwell.

1831
01:57:29,858 --> 01:57:34,030
Nothing poetic about that. I would've
taken it for the touchdown all the way.

1832
01:57:34,342 --> 01:57:36,948
That's his
sixth catch of the night.

1833
01:57:36,949 --> 01:57:39,160
Split to the right. Swenson
looks that way, hits him.

1834
01:57:39,347 --> 01:57:42,007
It's enough for a first
down at the 19-yard line.

1835
01:57:42,008 --> 01:57:45,918
Another savage hit
across the middle on Rod Tidwell.

1836
01:57:45,919 --> 01:57:48,264
He took some
shot, didn't he?

1837
01:57:48,265 --> 01:57:52,071
They are working Tidwell.
What does daddy always say?

1838
01:57:52,072 --> 01:57:55,928
"It looks worse than it
really is." That's right.

1839
01:57:55,929 --> 01:57:58,473
He ain't gonna have
nothing left for next season.

1840
01:57:58,849 --> 01:58:00,882
Will you be quiet?
What'd I say?

1841
01:58:00,883 --> 01:58:04,375
Less than two minutes to play.
Dallas leading by three.

1842
01:58:04,377 --> 01:58:08,963
Second down and one now at
the Dallas 11-yard line.

1843
01:58:08,964 --> 01:58:12,821
Hut! Swenson back to pass.
A blitz! Down he goes.

1844
01:58:12,822 --> 01:58:15,377
He's sacked for a six-yard loss.

1845
01:58:15,378 --> 01:58:18,349
Good move coming with
the blitz, getting after swenson.

1846
01:58:18,350 --> 01:58:20,957
Swenson's limping back.
He had too many men in that pattern.

1847
01:58:20,958 --> 01:58:24,501
They did not have enough
to pick up the blitz.

1848
01:58:24,502 --> 01:58:26,588
Listen up. Shut up!

1849
01:58:26,589 --> 01:58:30,655
- Ninety Razor, x out, on one.
- Ready? Break!

1850
01:58:30,656 --> 01:58:32,948
Okay, here we go.
Here we go.

1851
01:58:32,949 --> 01:58:36,078
He had a chance to get rid
of it, but he had to tuck it away.

1852
01:58:36,079 --> 01:58:39,623
From second and one,
they've now gone to third and seven.

1853
01:58:39,832 --> 01:58:43,481
In the waning moments of this
game, Dallas 17, Arizona 14.

1854
01:58:43,482 --> 01:58:45,879
- Set!
- Come on, card...

1855
01:58:45,880 --> 01:58:49,008
Tidwell in motion,
moving back to his left now.

1856
01:58:49,425 --> 01:58:54,119
Play fake. Swenson protected
well, lofts one to the end zone.

1857
01:58:54,536 --> 01:58:56,329
- Yeah!
- Touchdown Cardinals!

1858
01:58:56,517 --> 01:58:58,498
What a great effort!
Did you see him go up on that ball?

1859
01:58:58,915 --> 01:59:02,513
He held on to the football.
He's still down on the ground.

1860
01:59:02,515 --> 01:59:05,589
But Rod Tidwell, upside-down,
hits the ground hard...

1861
01:59:05,902 --> 01:59:08,457
And manages to maintain
control of the football.

1862
01:59:08,458 --> 01:59:10,488
He's hurt too.
Yeah.

1863
01:59:10,490 --> 01:59:14,035
He's not getting up.

1864
01:59:14,036 --> 01:59:17,529
- Look at the faces of these Cardinal players.
- Get up, baby.

1865
01:59:17,531 --> 01:59:19,979
Elation turns into concern
for their fallen teammate.

1866
01:59:19,980 --> 01:59:22,171
Cardinal trainer
comes onto the field...

1867
01:59:22,172 --> 01:59:24,258
As Tidwell makes his ninth catch
of the night... Oh, my God.

1868
01:59:24,259 --> 01:59:27,699
And gives Arizona
the lead. Hey!

1869
01:59:31,452 --> 01:59:33,485
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

1870
01:59:33,486 --> 01:59:36,613
Rod, can you hear me?
tRAINER #2: Blink, baby.

1871
01:59:36,614 --> 01:59:38,647
Come on, blink. Rod.

1872
01:59:38,960 --> 01:59:41,983
♪♪

1873
01:59:44,018 --> 01:59:45,998
Welcome back to...

1874
01:59:45,999 --> 01:59:49,128
Why are they going to a commercial?
Tell me what's wrong with my husband.

1875
01:59:49,129 --> 01:59:52,411
I told you he was too small
for the NFL. Shut up!

1876
01:59:52,412 --> 01:59:55,540
I got a commitment to the truth. I'm not
putting him down. I'm keeping it real.

1877
01:59:55,541 --> 01:59:57,627
Tee Pee, shut up!

1878
01:59:58,044 --> 02:00:00,598
Can't you be loyal to your
brother that loves you?

1879
02:00:00,599 --> 02:00:03,101
Get the hell outta my house.
Get out of my house!

1880
02:00:03,102 --> 02:00:07,221
Get out of my house, Tee Pee! Hello?
Hold on. It's Jerry Maguire!

1881
02:00:07,222 --> 02:00:09,619
Punk!

1882
02:00:12,017 --> 02:00:15,146
Jerry? Oh, my God, Jerry,
I am freaking out.

1883
02:00:15,147 --> 02:00:17,022
Marcee, he's unconscious.

1884
02:00:17,023 --> 02:00:21,611
Jerry, Jerry... I know. Just stay calm.
Keep the phone lines open.

1885
02:00:21,612 --> 02:00:25,626
I will call you back. There's good
doctors on the field. Stay calm.

1886
02:00:25,627 --> 02:00:29,536
You have to tell me something.
I cannot stay calm. I am freaking here.

1887
02:00:29,538 --> 02:00:33,604
Please. You gotta stay calm. Your
family needs you to stay calm.

1888
02:00:33,605 --> 02:00:35,584
I know,

1889
02:00:35,585 --> 02:00:38,713
But my whole life
is this family,

1890
02:00:39,026 --> 02:00:42,676
And it does not
work without him!

1891
02:00:42,677 --> 02:00:46,118
As we look at
it from another angle...

1892
02:00:46,119 --> 02:00:49,037
Jerry, I am so sorry...

1893
02:00:49,038 --> 02:00:51,749
Everything that I
said about your job.

1894
02:00:51,750 --> 02:00:55,502
Just do whatever you can
